Articles.Content: Please don't--they're wonderful engines, and we're really glad you published them. I can't speak for anyone but myself, but I was (I thought) only suggesting a trick you could use to decrease both file size and footprint in RAM without decreasing detail at all, not in the least criticizing the work you've done and are doing.

Please don't--they're wonderful engines, and we're really glad you published them. I can't speak for anyone but myself, but I was (I thought) only suggesting a trick you could use to decrease both file size and footprint in RAM without decreasing detail at all, not in the least criticizing the work you've done and are doing.

Nathan - as much as I would generally agree with you, this case is exception - if you would've seen these engines in reality, you'd pick up many subtle things that make these engines look so real - I had been fortunate enough to see most of these engines in reality - and I have to say and no other mod gets even close to this. THAT feeling costs a lot - I'm going to go as far as to say no other modpack/mod/model gets even close to this one on realism.

asmi, I'm not talking about reducing any detail. I'm talking about taking advantage of .20 and above features in KSP partloading to avoid using duplicate textures (which this pack has). If all models are in the same folder, they can share their identical textures and not force KSP/Unity to load multiple copies of the same texture. That's all.

You don't even have to use MODEL nodes.

EDIT for clarity: That said. BobCat, in whatever form you release things, they will be amazing; as I said above I massively respect what you do and if you want to totally ignore this suggestion (and any other I may) you're more than welcome to. Apologies for adding to an unhelpful chorus.

Edited November 16, 2013 by NathanKell

Russian Engine design has always been innovative efficient and fully functional years ahead of the west, the modelling of these engines is tribute to you and your country and I have huge respect for you and your country and I thank-you for giving us the opportunity to play with them in KSP

asmi, I'm not talking about reducing any detail. I'm talking about taking advantage of .20 and above features in KSP partloading to avoid using duplicate textures (which this pack has). If all models are in the same folder, they can share their identical textures and not force KSP/Unity to load multiple copies of the same texture. That's all.

That's what I was talking about, too. I was able to shave about 40% off Soviet Pack's size, without the slightest compromise in quality. Unfortunately, it requires revising the rescale factors and a lot of folder restructuring.

Oh, and the models themselves are great. I really love the giant RD-0120. Now, if only there was a procedural quad adapter included in StretchySRB...

Also, do you think you could model RD-117/118 (identical except for the number of verniers)? And expanding nozzle for RD-0146?

He was doing these models for me, and I don't care about texture size. If you don't like them - simply don't use them.

That's a very childish response. The dude was only offering constructive criticism that just happens to be completely valid.

It's not about like or dislike... these engines are awesome. He was offering advice onto how to make them even more awesome. Simple.

Hey

Great work on ECLSS support,

But the RemoteTech2_Release_1.2.0 seems to cancel ECLSS support system from the American pack 1,0.

I have testede this with a clean install:

KSP + American pack = ECLSS support

KSP + American pack +Romte tech 1,2 = no ECLSS support (vessels ECLSS IVA control panel says 0 to all resources)

Deleted remote tech 1,2 againe and ECLSS support is back

I'm starting to slowly feel sorry that they published these engines. It would be better if they had stayed at that who commissioned them.

Oh don't feel bad about that! You're my favorite modder and your mods are the finest KSP has ever seen!
I'm actually a bit surprised. Bobcat released a bunch of Russian rocket engines, and not one mention of Kosmos pack. *lights the bonfire*
Kosmos has a better RD-0146 (with a realistic nozzle). It's NK-33 about as detailed as BobCat's. Other than that, the engines don't overlap.
As much as I like bobcat's work, I use cbbp's pack for station and rocket building
I use, enjoy and appreciate both packs. I am constantly blown away by the attention to detail by these two great modders. Thank you BobCat (CBBP if you read this).

As much as I like bobcat's work, I use cbbp's pack for station and rocket building

Just keep in mind that Kosmos engines are very underpowered for RSS right now, somebody needs to write a realistic config for them to get them usable with RSS.

Perhaps you're missing the interiors. I've encountered a similar crippling bug when testing the American Pack. BobCat forgot to package the Orion interior one time and I ended up with a very similar lockout. If the interior is defined, but not found, you can expect this to happen.

Thanks, I've encountered it just now I didn't know that interiors are so necessary ))

I just can delete this string from cfg without any problem, right?
Yes, this should fix it, though you'll miss the interiors out.
